## 5. Repository Impact (given OPTION B)

This is deliberately a short list, because Option B's entire point is that most of the machinery already exists.

| Area | Change |
|---|---|
| **Domain model** | No new domain. Add `'visual_identity'` (or similarly named) to the existing 25-value `TaxonomyCategory` union in `types/entities.ts`, with a `stabilityClass` mapping consistent with §3 (lean `permanent` for palette/typography, `long_term` for mood/motion) added to `ObservationBuilder.stabilityClassFor()`'s existing switch. |
| **Entities** | No new entities. Extend `ArtifactPattern` (or its `sections`/`narrativeModel` sub-shape) with an optional visual-structure field, used only by artifact types where it's meaningful (decks, designed documents) — left absent/default for purely textual artifact types. Extend `ArtifactExemplar.structuralSnapshot` similarly. |
| **Events** | One new event type for "visual knowledge asset uploaded/analyzed" if the extraction is async (mirroring the existing `knowledge_asset.uploaded` pattern) — not a new event *category*, an additional member of the existing `IntelligenceEventType` union. (Note: per the Bootstrap's Gap Analysis G-1, this should use the already-recommended neutral naming, e.g. `knowledge_asset.visual_analyzed`, not a `brandos.*`-prefixed name.) |
| **Learning Pipeline** | No structural change. `SignalExtractor`/`ObservationBuilder` need a new `SourceQuality` consideration if visual signals arrive with different reliability characteristics than text (e.g., a VLM-derived description should probably sit below `uploaded_artifact`'s confidence ceiling, closer to `inferred`, since it's a model's interpretation of an asset rather than the asset's literal declared content — flagged but not resolved by the prior semantic analysis's evidence model, Deliverable 3). |
| **Blueprint Pipeline** | See §6 below — this is the one area with a real, specific integration design decision, not just a mechanical extension. |
| **Knowledge Pipeline** | **The one genuinely new component**: a `VisualFeatureExtractor` (or similarly named) class added to `knowledge/`, parallel to `VocabularyExtractor`/`FrameworkExtractor`/`PatternExtractor`, producing a structured result (the equivalent of `VocabularyExtractionResult`) rather than collapsing color/typography/mood into a single free-text blob — directly following the design correction the prior semantic analysis already specified for BrandOS's `E1-4` bridge (Deliverable 8). Whether this extractor does heuristic feature detection (palette extraction from an image, font-metadata parsing) or calls an external vision model is a real design decision the Bootstrap's Implementation Philosophy (§12) flags as needing design review before any pipeline component calls an external model — this decision should be made explicitly, not defaulted into, when the extractor is actually built. |
| **Storage** | No new tables. `intelligence.knowledge_assets`'s existing `extracted_patterns`/`extracted_frameworks` JSONB columns, or a new sibling `extracted_visual_features` JSONB column on the same table, hold the new extractor's output — schema.sql gets one additive column, not a new table family. |
| **Package structure** | No change. The new extractor lives in `packages/intelligence-os/src/knowledge/`, the existing package. |
| **Public interfaces** | No change to the four-method `IntelligenceOS` public surface (Architectural Rule 7 is preserved exactly). `ingestKnowledgeAsset()` already accepts an `assetType`; a visual asset type is a new enum value passed through the existing method, not a new method. |
| **Tests** | New unit tests for the new extractor (in `tests/unit/knowledge/`, alongside the existing extractor tests — see `intelligence-os-knowledge/AGENT_CONTEXT.md`'s existing testing-expectations guidance, which already anticipates new extractors needing exact-match deterministic assertions). No new integration-test *file* needed — the existing `tests/integration/blueprint.test.ts` and `intelligence-os.test.ts` gain new scenarios, not new files. |

